iter (2026-05-28, 0.1.611): FIXED browser-session crosstalk (user-flagged: agents closing each others browsers). ROOT CAUSE: plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js acquireProfileDir(cwd) keyed the chromium profile ONLY by cwd, so concurrent agent sessions in the same project contended for .gm/browser-profile and the collision/reclaim logic closed peer live browsers; the isProfileLocked fallback was per-watcher-pid (non-unique across sessions sharing one watcher). FIX: acquireProfileDir(cwd, claudeSessionId) -> per-session .gm/browser-profile-<sid> via sessionProfileDir+sessionProfileSlug; wantProfile uses the same per-sid path; cleanDeadProfileFragments only reaps unlocked or dead-pid dirs (never a peers live browser). ports/sessions maps were already per-sid-keyed. Per-session chromium = no crosstalk. Also validated supervisor exit-75 fix live (supervisor.watcher-exited-lock-rejected severity:info, no respawn storm).